cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.CY

The paper discusses the use of motion sensors on smartphones for device fingerprinting, which is a security and privacy concern, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) the most likely category. The study also involves a large-scale user study, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also explores countermeasures to protect privacy, which is related to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of sensors in web applications is also discussed, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
